Describe a piece of good news you heard about someone you know well
- What it was
- When you heard it
- How you knew it
- Explain how you felt about it

I’d like to talk about some great news I received about my younger brother, Tim, who is two years younger than me. About three months ago, I found out that he had been accepted into his dream university, which made me feel absolutely thrilled.

I heard the news from my mother. At the time, I was taking a nap when she called me to share the exciting update. As soon as I heard it, I jumped out of bed and was over the moon, because I knew how much effort he had put into achieving this goal.

To be honest, his success didn’t come easily. When he was in secondary school, he was just an average student, but everything changed when he entered high school. He became much more focused and disciplined, studying for several hours a day and even attending extra classes to improve his performance. He also gave up playing video games, which used to be one of his favorite pastimes, in order to concentrate on his studies.

Naturally, my whole family was delighted. My parents were incredibly proud and immediately shared the news with our relatives. That weekend, I went back home and we had a small, cozy celebration together, which was really memorable.

As for my brother, he had mixed feelings about starting this new chapter in his life. While he was excited about going to university, he was also a bit anxious about living away from home for the first time. Fortunately, everything has gone well so far, and he’s gradually adapting to his new environment.

Overall, I felt extremely happy and proud of him, as his achievement was truly the result of his hard work and determination.
